\section{Running interactive shell sessions}

The interactive variant forwards bytes between the PTY and the user's
terminal.  We temporarily switch stdin to raw mode so control characters
and line editing behave as they do in a normal shell session.

The relay loop must also notice when the PTY itself has closed.  Relying on
an empty [[select()]] result is not enough because a closed PTY often stays
readable at EOF.

<<functions>>=
def relay_interactive_shell(
    master_fd: int,
    process: subprocess.Popen,
    stdin_fd: int,
    stdout_fd: int,
) -> str:
    """Relay data between the user's terminal and a PTY-backed shell."""

    transcript = bytearray()
    master_open = True
    while True:
        readable, _, _ = select.select(
            [stdin_fd] + ([master_fd] if master_open else []),
            [],
            [],
            0.05,
        )

        if master_open and master_fd in readable:
            data = read_pty_output(master_fd)
            if data is None:
                master_open = False
            else:
                transcript.extend(data)
                os.write(stdout_fd, data)

        if stdin_fd in readable:
            data = os.read(stdin_fd, 4096)
            if data and master_open:
                os.write(master_fd, data)

        if process.poll() is not None and not master_open:
            break

    return transcript.decode("utf-8", errors="replace")
@

Let's also verify the relay exits as soon as the child is gone and the PTY
reports EOF.  That is the failure mode that previously left the tutorial
hanging after [[exit]].

<<test functions>>=
def test_relay_interactive_shell_stops_after_process_exit_and_pty_eof(
    monkeypatch,
):
    class FinishedProcess:
        def poll(self):
            return 0

    calls = {"select": 0}

    def fake_select(read_fds, write_fds, error_fds, timeout):
        calls["select"] += 1
        if calls["select"] > 1:
            raise AssertionError("relay loop did not stop after PTY EOF")
        return ([11], [], [])

    monkeypatch.setattr(select, "select", fake_select)
    monkeypatch.setattr(
        "pytorial.shell.read_pty_output",
        lambda master_fd: None,
    )

    transcript = relay_interactive_shell(11, FinishedProcess(), 12, 13)

    assert transcript == ""
    assert calls["select"] == 1
